Body:
Description: On running the SP Bulk Import Job we are encountering the following error :
We are seeing this error on both Y443 Dev server and on Production. 
(similar to a previous Ticket 370928) 

[C:23] Unable to perform bulk import Error: The MERGE statement conflicted with the FOREIGN KEY SAME TABLE constraint "FK_SA_SPAA_Resources_ParentId". The conflict occurred in database "J4D_STEALTHAUDIT_AEM_SP", table "dbo.SA_SPAA_Resources".
The statement has been terminated.

We planned to drop the SP tables and then rerun the scan and Bulk Import on the Production server.
However we are unable to drop the tables on the Production server - see attachment

@Ilya Kotov​ I have linked this to incident #[423577]​ 

 

The MERGE statement conflicted with the FOREIGN KEY constraint "<TableName>"

 

Please collect any missing artifacts and prepare an escalation @Damir Akhmatshin​
following the normal leadership meeting with AllState I have received the required artifacts and raised this to R&D.

What We've Learned Updated: The Level 2 scan completed - no sensitive data yet and there were some errors but OK to proceed to Level 3.
 
Level 3 has been running for a couple of days with scope ~400 sites. This is long and challenging. 
Allstate recognizes one reason for this is the dev environment is not performance provisioned as well as PROD.. But still, its long for only 400 sites.

Next Steps Updated: Stop the level 3 scan --> apply the new license --> reduce scope from 400 to 20 sites in order to get Level 3 scan complete in reasonable time. 

we will be able to bring in partial data via bulk import from existing scan into the new scan and see if there are any results to look at.

What We've Learned Updated: Level 3 scan against 20 sites completed successfully. Customer initaited scan to 4 levels on 20 sites.

Allstate recognizes one reason for this is the dev environment is not performance provisioned as well as PROD.. But still, its long for only 400 sites.
Steps to Reproduce Updated: Couldn't reproduce
QA engineer is still reviewing - expected to be released soon
The fix for this issue is published to CU NEA v11.6.0.138
